1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,440
[David Wheeler]: Real world programs often call out to other programs.

2
00:00:04,440 --> 00:00:09,870
On a server side application, these programs might include the operating system or a database.

3
00:00:09,870 --> 00:00:13,814
On a client side application, this might include the supporting browser.

4
00:00:14,670 --> 00:00:19,320
This chapter describes how to call other programs securely.

5
00:00:19,320 --> 00:00:26,097
We'll discuss, in particular, on how to counter injection attacks, including SQL injection and OS command injection,

6
00:00:26,611 --> 00:00:30,033
as well as how to properly handle file names and path names.

